{"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/51746", "repository_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust", "labels_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/51746/labels{/name}", "comments_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/51746/comments", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/51746/events", "html_url": "https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/51746", "id": 335132518, "node_id": "MDU6SXNzdWUzMzUxMzI1MTg=", "number": 51746, "title": "Take does not reserve its limit on read_to_end", "user": {"login": "MichaelTheriot", "id": 3187409, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMxODc0MDk=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3187409?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/MichaelTheriot", "html_url": "https://github.com/MichaelTheriot", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/MichaelTheriot/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/MichaelTheriot/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/MichaelTheriot/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/MichaelTheriot/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/MichaelTheriot/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/MichaelTheriot/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/MichaelTheriot/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/MichaelTheriot/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/MichaelTheriot/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "labels": [{"id": 113376, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxMTMzNzY=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/I-slow", "name": "I-slow", "color": "e10c02", "default": false, "description": "Problems and improvements with respect to performance of generated code."}, {"id": 234902, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMzQ5MDI=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/C-enhancement", "name": "C-enhancement", "color": "f5f1fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: An issue proposing an enhancement or a PR with one."}, {"id": 211668062, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMTE2NjgwNjI=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/T-libs-api", "name": "T-libs-api", "color": "bfd4f2", "default": false, "description": "Relevant to the library API team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue."}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2018-06-23T21:31:47Z", "updated_at": "2018-08-05T05:39:50Z", "closed_at": "2018-08-01T22:06:33Z", "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Using `readable.take(x).read_to_end(&mut buf)` can cause the capacity of `buf` to exceed what is needed.\r\n\r\n**I tried this code:**\r\n\r\n```rust\r\nuse std::io::Read;\r\n\r\nfn main() {\r\n    let readable = &[1];\r\n    let mut buf: Vec<u8> = Vec::with_capacity(2);\r\n\r\n    assert_eq!(buf.len(), 0);\r\n    assert_eq!(buf.capacity(), 2);\r\n    readable.take(1).read_to_end(&mut buf).unwrap();\r\n\r\n    assert_eq!(buf.len(), 1);\r\n    assert_eq!(buf.capacity(), 32);\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nhttps://play.rust-lang.org/?gist=83401a704fddcec007bcfb0ecc85fc6d&version=nightly&mode=debug\r\n\r\n**I expected to see this happen:**\r\n`readable.take(1)` should reserve `1`.\r\n\r\n`Take` should reserve a maximum of `take.limit()`.\r\n\r\n**Instead, this happened:**\r\n`buf` capacity increased because `readable.take(1)` reserved `32` which exceeds its `limit`.\r\n\r\n`Take` will [always reserve in increments of `32`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/src/std/io/mod.rs.html#372) rather than its known `limit`.\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\nI'm new to Rust; my guess is implementing `read_to_end` specifically for `Take` is the way to improve this.", "closed_by": {"login": "bors", "id": 3372342, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjMzNzIzNDI=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3372342?